$ HTMLElement.offset*

This example tries to demonstrate the `→ development/web/HTML/DOM/API/interfaces-classes/HTMLElement` propertes `offsetParent`, `offsetLeft`, `offsetTop`, `offsetWidth` and `offsetHeight`.
gh|about-HTML-DOM-API|/HTMLElement/offset_.html||

When executed, the following is logged in the console window:
code {
one
  parent:       body
  left/top      20@10
  width/height: 180x90
two
  parent:       one
  left/top      35@15
  width/height: 125x55
three
  parent:       two
  left/top      12@12
  width/height: 48x12
code }

sa:

  `→ development/web/HTML/DOM/API/interfaces-classes/HTMLElement`
